replies.body:
Actually yeah, you aren't supposed to understand it, but it IS mashed up versions of her old quote system. For example, around 1:30, it sounds like she says "fanf-ends-a symph" which is really close to a recutting of "the fanfare ascends" and "a symphony of justice." At 1:37, it sounds like "uar-er-ime-uet" or "quarter time" and "a sublime duet." All of the quotes are like this, good job Riot!

Also the main reason I picked up on this is A) I've played Sona for a year and a half and B) I like listening to the dialogue of my favorite characters. For example, I also know most of the quotes from the Emerald Herald in Dark Souls II.

EDIT: Oh man this makes me sound crazy, but I just really like her quotes. I can't wait for the hotfixes to go live so I can test out the skin. {{champion:37}}

tho, i'd like to drop, that probably Oriannas voice sounds more fitting in my opinion;
well yeah, she has a robotic/glados like voice, but it'd probably would solve the voice over problem for dj sona being hard to hear, yet being extremly well fitting.
as well don't forget for those players who probably deactivate the music as dj sona..
